Package: CompHeatmaps
Type: Package
Title: Generating Heatmaps from Raw 16S rRNA Reads
Version: 1.0.1
Author: Koji Wong (koji.wong@mail.utoronto.ca)
Maintainer: The package maintainer <koji.wong@mail.utoronto.ca>
Description: This package takes raw 16S rRNA reads across a number of
    samples to eventually generate a heatmap of the abundance. It first
    preprocesses the data using dada2, creates an abundance table also
    using dada2, and creates a heatmap using gplots. 
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 4.3.1)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
biocViews: Classification, ImmunoOncology, Metagenomics, Microbiome, Sequencing, Software
Imports: 
    dada2 (>= 1.30),
    dplyr (>= 1.1.3),
    ggplot2 (>= 3.4.4),
    shiny (>= 1.8.0),
    tibble (>= 3.2.1)
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/kojiwong/CompHeatmaps
